Author: Zodiac
Number: 21.10.2014
Description:
This programme is to synchronise a source file and a destination.
Usage: 
After compile all java files to jar files, you can use following 
command to run this programme. 
* java -jar synserver.jar -file filename [-p serverport]
* java -jar synclient.jar -file filename -host hostname[-p serverport]
[-b blocksize] [-d direction] 

P.S: options of direction are "push" and "pull". "push" will push
local files to remote server. "pull" will pull a local file from
remote server to client


